    "17 Our calculations show that the 90 papers leaked data from 263 unique datasets, for a total of over 4.7M samples (see Tables 4 to 6 in the Appendix).",
    "18 We find most samples (∼ 93.8%) coming from datasets treated as whole (with no split), followed by test and development (∼ 5.6%), 19 and training (∼ 0.6%) sets.",
    "In line with what we discussed in Section 3, we can conclude that ChatGPT was exposed to millions of benchmark samples, enriched with instructions that could be considered de-facto novel gold-standard data in some cases.",
